ch tradition and, in particular, its separation of theory and ethnographic practice. Finally, Silverman traces the formative influence of Franz Boas, the expansion of the discipline after World War II, and the "fault lines" and promises of contemporary anthropology in the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aanthropology, fieldwork, international, discipline, social sciences, sociology, academia, scholarship, ethnography, england, britain, germany, france, sydel silverman, robert parkin, andre gingrich, fredrik barth, max planck institute, franz boas, nazi, third reich, culture, hierarchy, superiority, primitive, nonfiction, history, philosophy, argonauts, torres straits, radcliffe-brown, malinowski, volkskunde, enlightenment, nationalism, diffusionism, subaltern, competition, collaboration, marxism, structuralism, persecution, materialism.1 aBarth, Fredrik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGingrich, Andre, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGingrich, Andre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aParkin, Robert, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aParkin, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilverman, Sydel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106353860 cprintz978022603828540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226038278423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226038278/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles